around the
boat. So, by the time the
plywood get boxed,

46:04.128 --> 46:12.937 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
the next time, everybody was
running, scattering,
running, run to this side, run
to this side,

46:12.970 --> 46:20.945 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
run to this side. Then the fuel
was not mixing
with the water. And we were
taking buckets,

46:20.978 --> 46:26.584 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
start baling the water out of
the boat, baling
water out of the boat. But the
water was still

46:26.617 --> 46:28.386 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
gushing inside.

46:28.419 --> 46:34.258 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
DENNIS OSBI, Survivor: I think
the rushing
of the men coming forward to
where we were

46:34.291 --> 46:39.163 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
